# 🩺 dbt-doctor

> **AI-driven quality & governance MCP Server for dbt projects.**

[![CI](https://github.com/yourusername/dbt-doctor/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/yourusername/dbt-doctor/actions/workflows/ci.yml)
[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/dbt-doctor.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/dbt-doctor)
[![Python 3.10+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10%2B-blue.svg)](https://python.org)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE)

dbt-doctor gives your AI assistant (Claude, Cursor, Copilot) deep awareness of your dbt project's health, connecting the power of MCP to automated auditing, data profiling, schema drift detection and documentation generation — all in one tool.

> Works great alongside the official [dbt-labs/dbt-mcp](https://github.com/dbt-labs/dbt-mcp)

---

## 🔑 Key Features (12 MCP Tools)

| Category | Tool | What it does |
|---|---|---|
| **Context** | `list_models` | All models with doc status, coverage |
| **Context** | `get_model_details` | SQL, columns, lineage, tests |
| **Audit** | `audit_project` | Health score (0-100%), violations list |
| **Audit** | `check_test_coverage` | Ranked models by test coverage |
| **Audit** | `analyze_dag` | Orphans, max depth, high fan-out |
| **Audit** | `get_project_health` | **Entry point:** one-stop dashboard |
| **Profiling** | `profile_model` | NULL%, unique%, min/max per column |
| **Profiling** | `execute_query` | Read-only SQL to DWH |
| **Profiling** | `detect_schema_drift` | DB columns vs manifest — find drift |
| **Generation** | `suggest_tests` | Profile stats → concrete test list |
| **Generation** | `update_model_yaml` | Write docs/tests to schema.yml |
| **Generation** | `generate_model_docs` | **Killer feature:** E2E auto-documentation |

---

## ⚡ Quick Start

```bash
pip install dbt-doctor
```

For Claude Desktop, add to `claude_desktop_config.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "dbt-doctor": {
      "command": "dbt-doctor",
      "args": ["--project-dir", "/absolute/path/to/your/dbt/project"]
    }
  }
}
```

For **Cursor**, add to `.cursor/mcp.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "dbt-doctor": {
      "command": "dbt-doctor",
      "args": ["--project-dir", "/absolute/path/to/your/dbt/project"]
    }
  }
}
```

Then in Claude: _"Audit my dbt project and generate docs for the worst covered model."_

---

## 🔧 How It Works

```
Your dbt project
     │
     ├── target/manifest.json  ←── dbt-doctor reads this (run `dbt compile` first)
     ├── dbt_project.yml       ←── reads profile name
     └── models/               ←── reads/writes schema.yml files
                                        │
                                        ▼
                             dbt-doctor MCP Server
                         ┌─────────────────────────────┐
                         │  Audit   Profile   Generate  │
                         │  Score   Profile   YAML      │
                         │  DAG     Drift     E2E docs  │
                         └─────────────────────────────┘
                                        │
                                        ▼
                                Your AI Assistant
                           (Claude / Cursor / Copilot)
```

### Supported Databases

| Adapter | Status |
|---------|--------|
| PostgreSQL | ✅ Full support |
| DuckDB | ✅ Full support (zero-config) |
| BigQuery, Snowflake, Redshift | 🔜 Planned |

---

## 🎭 Example Workflow

**"Document the fct_orders model":**

```
AI → get_project_health
     ← Score: 42%. fct_orders is worst covered.

AI → generate_model_docs("fct_orders")
     ← Profile: 1.2M rows, order_id is 100% unique & not null
       Suggestions: not_null + unique on order_id, accepted_values on status

AI → update_model_yaml("fct_orders",
       description="Customer orders with lifetime value",
       columns=[{order_id: [not_null, unique]}, {status: [accepted_values]}])
     ← ✅ Written to models/marts/_fct_orders.yml

AI → detect_schema_drift("fct_orders")
     ← ✅ No drift — DB matches documentation.
```

---

## 🏗️ Project Structure

```
src/dbt_doctor/
├── server.py           # FastMCP server (12 tools)
├── core/               # Manifest, profiles, project parsers
├── connectors/         # Postgres, DuckDB (extensible base ABC)
├── analyzers/          # Auditor, profiler, drift detector, DAG
├── generators/         # Test suggester, YAML writer, E2E doc gen
└── utils/              # SQL sanitizer, formatters
```

